    {
      "name": "Get Listing Calendar",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token}}",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/listings/{{listingId}}/calendar?from=2026-04-01&to=2026-04-30",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "listings",
            "{{listingId}}",
            "calendar"
          ],
          "query": [
            {
              "key": "from",
              "value": "2026-04-01",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "key": "to",
              "value": "2026-04-30",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        "description": "## Important Thing to Understand About the Calendar\n\nThe `minNights` value on the **check-in date** is what matters. So when your WordPress site shows a calendar to the user, you need to:\n\n1. When a user picks a check-in date, look up `minNights` for that date\n    \n2. Automatically block all checkout dates that are less than `minNights` away\n    \n3. Only allow checkout dates that satisfy the minimum\n    \n\nThis is standard behavior on all vacation rental sites ŌĆö you'll implement this logic in your calendar UI later.  \n  \nAlso Note the `blocks` Object\n\nYour calendar response has a `blocks` field on each date that tells you _why_ something is unavailable. Here's what each key means:\n\n| Key | Meaning |\n| --- | --- |\n| `b` | **Booked** ŌĆö has a reservation |\n| `r` | Reserved (inquiry pending) |\n| `m` | Manually blocked by host |\n| `bd` | Blocked due to booking window |\n| `sr` | Sync restriction |\n| `a` | Advance notice block |\n| `o` | Owner block |\n| `pt` | Preparation time (turnover day) |\n| `cta` | Closed to arrival |\n| `ctd` | Closed to departure |\n\nIn your data, only `b: true` is firing, meaning these dates are simply booked by guests."
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "Create a Quote (Price Calculation)",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "var response = pm.response.json();",
              "if (response._id) {",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(\"quoteId\", response._id);",
              "    console.log(\"Quote ID saved: \" + response._id);",
              "    console.log(\"Expires at: \" + response.expiresAt);",
              "}",
              "if (response.rates && response.rates.ratePlans && response.rates.ratePlans.length > 0) {",
              "    var ratePlanId = response.rates.ratePlans[0].ratePlan._id;",
              "    pm.collectionVariables.set(\"ratePlanId\", ratePlanId);",
              "    console.log(\"Rate Plan ID saved: \" + ratePlanId);",
              "    ",
              "    // Log the price breakdown",
              "    var money = response.rates.ratePlans[0].ratePlan.money;",
              "    console.log(\"Accommodation: \" + money.fareAccommodation);",
              "    console.log(\"Cleaning fee: \" + money.fareCleaning);",
              "    console.log(\"Taxes: \" + money.totalTaxes);",
              "    console.log(\"Total: \" + money.subTotalPrice);",
              "}"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript",
            "packages": {},
            "requests": {}
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "key": "Authorization",
            "value": "Bearer {{token}}",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"listingId\": \"{{listingId}}\",\n  \"checkInDateLocalized\": \"2026-04-07\",\n  \"checkOutDateLocalized\": \"2026-04-09\",\n  \"guestsCount\": 2\n}",
          "options": {
            "raw": {
              "language": "json"
            }
          }
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/reservations/quotes",
          "host": [
            "{{baseUrl}}"
          ],
          "path": [
            "api",
            "reservations",
            "quotes"
          ]
        }
      },
      "response": []
    },
